### TypeScript and React style

- Use explicit types for public APIs and function returns; avoid `any`.
- Prefer descriptive names; avoid abbreviations.
- Use early returns and handle errors explicitly; avoid deep nesting.
- Do not catch and ignore errors. Bubble with context or return typed results.
- Match existing formatting and ESLint rules in [`eslint.config.mjs`](mdc:eslint.config.mjs).
- In Client Components, avoid heavy server-only modules; in Server Components, avoid browser-only APIs.
- Import from app aliases consistently; keep imports sorted and deduplicated.
